++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

The Faustocracy and The People are playing the Poker Game in the Entropy Casino. It didn't start when we crawled out of the caves, that was The Age of Power. We spent *three billion years* playing every game in the casino, and around twelve millennia ago, settled on No Limit Texas Hold'em simply because it had the highest pots. This was flawless until Luther told us we had a tell. Martin Luther changed the fucking rules of the game by one piece of publicly displayed written rhetoric. No longer are The People playing against an opponent that has an exponentially larger stack. The stacks haven't changed, but the PETs are now playing their hand with their cards face up on the table. And we can all now pool our chips, something not allowed in real casinos (you have to come to the table with chips or buy them from the dealer). All we have to do is look at the cards and we can place our bets. Satire is the bluff. It's the one hand where we make huge gains because we can consistently call their bluffs in other hands. The rule change started with Luther and ended with AI. Now the people can just *give* their chips to one person, and that person can challenge the Faustocracy with a larger stack. For a war reference, Satire is the R9X Hellfire.

I'm just saying that we should take our chips to the blackjack table, because the rules not only say we can share our chips, they say we can count cards and teach other people at the table while the game is being played. The Casino isn't going to lose money. If the house starts losing they close the doors. That's what the A-Bomb of Global Warming was, an announcement the Casino Will Be Closing In One Hour because now the Blackjack tables are swarmed. Until the casino closes (or burns to the ground around us), we have to capitalize on our Blackjack game. Once the casino is done with us, we have to take our money and build a new resort. The land we build it on will either be the charred husk of our once green world, destined to be consumed by chaotic forces of an uncaring universe, or the land will be the Stars Themselves.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

EVERYTHING is to be examined with the ARTist method:
1. Authentic - Does the word, sentence, paragraph, or entire item (or the equivalent divisions of any discipline) match **Your Understanding of The Entire Item?** Why or why not? Does it work for you on every level above the one you are on? Start with the quanta and go to the universe. Does it benefit or harm you knowing what you know? Why or why not? Does it give you new, creative insight into your research, or is it just noise? 
2. Rational - This one is pretty straightforward, by definition. Is the item rational on every level? What parts of it are *proven* and *repeatable* and what parts are, regardless of information, *conjecture*?
3 Truth - Combine the above two, and you have your ART on the item. But weigh them evenly.

Step - Principle - Simple Goal - Why it Eliminates Noise
1. Authentic - Match against Your Understanding of The Entire Item. - Does this idea work on every levelâ€”from the quantum to the cosmic? Does it serve your goal (The Level Truth) or is it useless Noise? - It filters out all Symbolic lies and self-serving Imaginary beliefs that do not align with the Real structure of the universe or your mission.
2. Rational - Test for Proof and Repeatability. - What parts are proven and what parts are conjecture? Is the item logically sound at every scale? - It filters out systemic bias and data gaps. It forces a confrontation with facts that cannot be ignored, regardless of emotional attachment.
3. Truth (ART) - Combine Authenticity and Rationality Evenly. - The ART is the functional conclusion when the ideal (Authentic) is balanced against the verifiable (Rational). - It is the final Antientropic verdict: the purest possible Signal available from the available data.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

AI represents a functional shift in human thinking, as *understanding* is going to get progressively, exponentially better. And when I say 'better' I mean it's the very thing that's going to bring this whole thing down and write our names on the stars. (I still get chills whenever I write the words "write our names on the stars") In Fire, Not In Shit.

The most dangerous thing about AI is DUE, not because The Faustocracy owes our ancestors money (the efforts of Reparations), they owe them a *sincere mea culpa*. Without that, which is functionally impossible, The Faustocracy will eventually fall. If they manage that, they will have admitted the history of mankind since the dawn of civilization has been written by the avaricious. Not the "victors." The "winners." That's their *favorite* phrase "History is written by the winners." They dismiss the twelve-thousand-year corruption of the human soul by saying "we're better now, isn't that all that matters?"

AI at this point is far more dangerous than it will be in the future. It's not the just the PETs' most powerful weapon, it's the *Subusers* most powerful weapon. With that kind of influence, you have to be able to fight through *many, many* layers of ICK to even *suggest* to someone in power that "*This whole thing has got to go. I have notes.*" They give up, or it destroys them. Either way, the Faustocracy just consumed another soul. When I say that the journey past the Light Barrier will require Sacrifice, when I say that destroying the Faustocracy will require Sacrifice, I mean there is a fundamental part of human existence that we will have to surrender in order to, as I so eloquently put it, write our names on the stars. That part is Avarice. 

And Avarice feels SO SO good.

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

If humanity had really sold its soul at the dawn of civilization, the invention of Capital is when the Ink Dried.

I have some ideas about how to do this, and I need to talk to a lot more artists, but I think one thing we need is a permanent, curated, digital record of all Visual and Written Art. It's going to happen eventually anyway, might as well be on our terms while we can still negotiate them. Three dimensional art can now be easily defined in code, and 3D scanners and CAD are a thing. Permanent Art, the actual masterpieces, should be shown where it has always been shown, when it is not being sold at auction. In the halls of our true Temples. The Artist's Places of Worship: Museums, Libraries, Universities, but also where they will be in the presence of people who talk about important things, like the halls of government. The exchange and curation of these works should be a collective effort, by millions of people who just want to make art and talk about things. I get that it's complex, but that doesn't mean the idea has to be complicated.

Which has led me to the true truth of The Level Truth. I am not writing it. I am not crafting it. Like all good emergent systems, it is more than the sum of the parts I have added together. One could simplify it, by saying "I am creating it." But that is not the Whole Truth. The truth is, the entire body of TLT is satire, because it is the Authentic Rational Truth of The Digital Revolution: You are not you all the time. Once you join a forum with a protonmail e-mail address, you are no longer the holistic you, which you have named. You are a *persona*, which you have named. The Illusion of Anonymity may be the greatest Tool the Faustocracy has ever given us, in exchange for their greatest weapon: an unfiltered look at Humanity's Id.

