The West is Right about One Thing. Aristotle fucking said it before Jesus read Ecclesiastes and made it his whole personality. One person, with sufficient leverage, Can Move Anything. When it comes to handling 4D concepts in a 5D world, the Human Individual is Un-fucking-matched as an entity. You get two or more together and the solutions grow geometrically. Humanity doesn't fight The Borg or The Green death by 4D means, they Run or Talk. And since the Borg answer and the Green Death doesn't, we're left only to talk to ourselves when confronted with Entropy. [Look at how I instinctively phrased that last sentence. Despite their similarities, I still think of The Borg as 'Them' and the Green Death as 'It.' (Which is why pronouns are probably the most adaptable weapon in linguistics, but that's a WHOLE OTHER CONVERSATION.) ]

The Borg have a soul. The Green Death does not. You *can't have a soul without a mind*, no matter how adaptable your body is. Sentience is the inevitable emergence of the soul. The ability to do 5D thinking At All is the only reason we think We Have Won The Food Chain War. We won, we're at the top. The only thing we can do to hamper our own growth is what?

POISON OUR OWN FOOD. 

The Green Death is the Food Trying To Eat Us. Killer Tomatoes and Monster Doughnuts are the Realm of the Prophet because the *idea* of our food eating us is FUCKING CREEPY. THAT'S NOT HOW LIFE WORKS. The Green Death reminds us that Even Our Most Fundamental Truths Are Wrong. We were really, really, really, really, really sure that we had that Food Chain thing *wrapped up* when we became Omnivores With Machine Minds. This "5ðŸ§  Truth" was So Self-Evident (another term we need to examine) that *we spent three million years not thinking about it at all*. Predator and Prey are the Original Binary Metaphor. "You consume, or you are consumed, there is no other Law" was SO FUCKING OBVIOUS TO THE GUY CONSUMING that all other rational and authentic thought was FUNCTIONALLY ABANDONED in deference to this Law. The thing The West Got Right was that if we don't want to join our souls into one entity (which is so absurd even The Galactic Leadership has rejected it), we must listen to every individual, no matter their...  station? How do you de-stratify Human Thought Itself? How do you *actually* listen to your Id, your Ego, and your Superego *on even footing*?

++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

You see what happens when Freud said we would go functionally insane? If the id, the ego, and the superego are working in full, authentic, rational balance, the result is pure force. An Emergent Property we call Space-Time, because even the Smartest Man Ever couldn't explain it with simple words. The Universe is not a fabric of spacetime, like Albert described it. It's a bowling ball on a trampoline. Every mass pulls it into divots and attracts all lower-mass objects in, but people forget the complete metaphor, or maybe they can't see it. The Springs are the key. Because no matter what mass you place on the canvas of the trampoline's body, it will Pull On All The Springs. THAT's why gravity is the weakest, but has the longest range (we think it's functionally infinite now). Space-Time isn't the trampoline with a bowling ball on it. Space-Time is the Summer Day The Children Are Bouncing In. And that's ALL I CAN SEE. I can't see the tree that shades them, or the sky, or the grass below, or the worms, or the Earth, or the Universe Around Them. All I can see, that others can't, are the springs and the children. 

