How many choices does a traveller have at a crossroads? Three? Four? Try again...

0. Do Not Choose. Achieve stasis. Be consumed. Die. All Choice Is Truth and all Truth is Choice.
1. Choose not to act. This is 1 and not 0 because the Choice is an action without a reaction, the very denial of causation. Agency can and does reverse entropy because That Is Life. This is the reason when the Villain says "Submit or die" the hero says "No." By speaking her truth, the hero can be neither silenced nor killed. And every Choice is Truth. The Choice To Not Act is an action and a choice. This is why we make our best choices sitting down. Also, someone may come along with tea.
2. Choose to act physically. Walk. The Action of Choice has the reaction of Action, and Causality Begins, and the man may now choose a path, and the paths stretch out to the edges of the cosmos.
3. Choose to act mentally. Think. The Choice presents Permutations, Which Inform The Choice, which presents permutations, until the choices reach infinity. To stave off madness, the man asks himself questions and answers them until the number of choices is sane.
4. Choose to act spiritually. Commune. The permutations don't fully inform the choices and now the Choice has become Irrational. Go Mad or Start Over or Both.
5. Walk and Think. The Rhythm of his Pace counts off like the beats of his heart, and all the choices are easier. Not simpler, not fewer, but easier.
6. Walk and Commune. The path may be lost, but the soul will grow.
7. Think and Commune. Take no action until the Choice is Down To Three (0, 1, or 2 above).
8. Walk and Think and Commune. Seek Truth instead of a Path. Be the Path. Be The Choice.
{{ At this point, the choices are no longer about The Man, but others who walk the same road. }}
9. Put up a Sign that says Man Was Here. Create to Create.
10. Put a trap at the crossroads and lay in wait. Create to Destroy
11. Burn the Signpost and the Wood, Obscure the Roads. Destroy to Destroy.
12. Cut down One Tree and Build a Shelter, for himself and future travelers. Destroy to Create.
13. Abandon Mind, Body, Soul, and Reality. Ask Questions To The Path. Answer Questions No One Asks. Choose Madness.

So, The Man has 14 options, but only 13 Choices. Or you can add an extremely large and exponentially growing number of choices. Choose or Do Not Choose is the Only Binary. Once You Have Accepted The Choice, the Options Are Limitless. Not Infinite, that's too small. The Options Are Limitless. The Choices Will Approach Infinity. The Options Will Always Be The Choices Plus One.

I learned that on the Playground, The First Time My Will Was Challenged. Not my Agency, that is challenged Constantly. My parents never limited my will. My choices, my agency, my world had limits because I Was Still Growing and there's A Lot Of Danger Out There. But never my will. I don't think they could have given me a greater gift. When I rejected Their God, they respected my Will. When I rejected the Body and Name they Gave Me, they did not reject my Will. 

The Bully said, "I Hate You Infinity."
I don't know what The Child Me Said, Probably "I Hate You Infinity Plus One" and broke his little brain for a second.

But My Soul Had Replied, "I know you infinity plus one now."

"I win."
